The paper deals with the classification of elementary cellular automata based on information theory and sensitivity to initial conditions. This involves analyzing transfer entropy variations processed by the system, which falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of cellular automata also suggests a connection to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the hierarchy of the information-based classes, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the study of complex systems and their behavior could also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
